{"word":"Τραχωνῖτις","slug":"Τραχωνῖτις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Τραχωνῖτις, ιδος, ἡ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:τραχύς\">τραχύς</a></el>] <b>Trachonitis,</b> a district south of Damascus; in <b><a href='B:490 3:1'>Lk 3:1</a></b> used as an <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adj.\">adj.</a> <el>ἡ Τ. <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:χώρα\">χώρα</a></el> the Trachonitis region. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:τραχύς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:τρεῖς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}